  "content": "<div><tt><br></tt></div>\n<div><tt>--___-''</tt></div>\n<div><tt><br></tt></div>\n<div><object><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; direction: ltr\">\n<tbody>\n<tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><br></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><div><i>So when I said to Chris, hey I have all these cameras, you should set up all these cameras so we could, we could tape all of the plays of the other people, and we could tape your play, and we could tape all the connective moments, and we could have all these different angles, and he said, basically, ah but the beauty of it is that it's in the moment. Why am I crying? Oh my god, I'm such a baby. The beauty of it, I guess I feel bad that I missed it, because I was supposed to be there, my life was falling apart, and I ran home to New York, and I missed it. I feel actually terrible about it, and honestly, I feel like I miss a lot of people's things. I only care about myself, and I think that's reflected in how people are sort of responding to me in a sense, but I could be being paranoid.</i></div>",
